data.chText: 暴君；专制君主；暴虐的统治者
data.enText: a person who has complete power in a country and uses it in a cruel and unfair way

data.chText: 这个国家接连遭受暴君的统治。
data.enText: The country was ruled by a succession of tyrants.

data.chText: 他的老板是个不折不扣的暴君。
data.enText: His boss is a complete tyrant.

tr: any person who exercises power in a cruel way
in ancient Greece, a ruler who had seized power without legal right to it

value.def: You can use tyrant to refer to someone who treats the people they have authority over in a cruel and unfair way.

example.ex: Since 1804 the country has mostly been ruled by tyrants.
example.tran: 自 1804 年以来，该国大部分时间都处于暴君的统治之下。

example.ex: ...households where the father was a tyrant.

value.tran: 暴君;专制君主;暴君似的人
